Introduction/Akizuki.Japanese: 秋月型防空駆逐艦、一番艦、秋月。ここに推参致しました。お任せください！
Introduction/Akizuki.English: Akizuki-class anti-air destroyer, first ship, Akizuki. I'm reporting in here. Please leave it to me!

Library/Akizuki.Japanese: 艦隊防空のために建造された乙型一等駆逐艦、秋月型駆逐艦一番艦、秋月です。4基8門の長10ｃｍ砲と高射装置を備えた防空艦として、寮艦の初月らと共に第61駆逐隊を編成しました。頑張ります！
Library/Akizuki.English: Designed for the fleet's anti-air, Type-B first class destroyer, Akizuki-class 1st destroyer, Akizuki. As an anti-air ship equipped with 4x 8-barrel Long 10cm guns and anti-aircraft fire director, along with Hatsuzuki and the others, we formed the 61st DesDiv. I'll do my best!

Secretary 2/Akizuki.Japanese: この秋月の長10cm砲と高射装置。この力で、艦隊をきっとお守りします！
Secretary 2/Akizuki.English: My long 10cm guns and anti-aircraft fire director. With this power, I'll definitely protect the fleet!

Secretary 2/Akizuki Kai.Japanese: 増設された高射装置と長10cm砲。秋月の本当の力…これで、艦隊をお守りします！
Secretary 2/Akizuki Kai.English: The added anti-aircraft fire director and long 10cm guns. Akizuki's real power... with this, I'll protect the fleet!

Secretary 3/Akizuki.Japanese: 長10cm砲ちゃん、あんまり暴れないでぇ！ あら、あらら？ 提…督？ ああっ、失礼致しました！
Secretary 3/Akizuki.English: Choujuusenchihou-chan, don't struggle! Eh, huh? Ad...miral? Ahh! Please excuse me!

Idle/Akizuki.Japanese: 長10cmよし、高射装置よし、酸素魚雷、よし…よし！ 万全ね、大丈夫！ えっと、あとは…
Idle/Akizuki.English: Long 10cm, check! Anti-aircraft fire director, check! Oxygen torpedoes, check... alright! Everything's perfect! Umm, next is...

Secretary Married/Akizuki.Japanese: 司令、いつもお疲れ様です。この秋月が、艦隊と司令をお護りします。だ、大丈夫！
Secretary Married/Akizuki.English: Commander, thanks as always. This Akizuki will protect the fleet, and you. Yeah, it's alright!

Wedding/Akizuki.Japanese: 司令、秋月をお呼びでしょうか？　あの、対空戦に不備が？　そうではなくって？　では、翔鶴さんになにか？　でもなくって？　…ほぁ、もしかして、これ…あ、ありがとうございます！
Wedding/Akizuki.English: Commander, did you call me? Um, was my anti-air inadequate? That's not it? Then does it have to do with Shoukaku-san? Not that either? ...Howaa~, could this be... T-thank you very much!

Looking At Scores/Akizuki.Japanese: そうですね。艦隊の今を知ることは、大事です！
Looking At Scores/Akizuki.English: That's true. It's important to know what the fleet knows!

Joining A Fleet/Akizuki.Japanese: 防空駆逐艦、秋月。出撃致します！
Joining A Fleet/Akizuki.English: Anti-air destroyer, Akizuki. Prepared to sortie.

Equipment 1/Akizuki.Japanese: ありがとうございます！よい装備…

Equipment 2/Akizuki.Japanese: これなら敵機動部隊にも負けません！
Equipment 2/Akizuki.English: With this, I won't lose to the enemy task force!

Equipment 3/Akizuki.Note: ⇧ shared with expedition selection, resource collection, instant repair and development

Supply/Akizuki.Japanese: 補給、ありがとうございます！

Supply/Akizuki Kai.Japanese: 大切な補給物資、ありがとうございます！
Supply/Akizuki Kai.English: Thank you for the important supply materials!

Docking Minor/Akizuki.English: J-just for a bit, I'll take a break...

Docking Major/Akizuki.Japanese: 高射装置も、しっかり装備しなくちゃ…
Docking Major/Akizuki.English: My anti-air fire director too, I need to firmly attach it...

Docking Complete/Akizuki.Japanese: 修理中の艦が、ドックを出るみたい。
Docking Complete/Akizuki.English: It seems that the under repairing ship leaves dock.

Construction/Akizuki.Japanese: 新造艦が生まれたみたいですね！
Construction/Akizuki.English: It seems like a new ship was born!

Returning From Sortie/Akizuki.Japanese: 艦隊が無事帰投しました。皆さん、お疲れです！
Returning From Sortie/Akizuki.English: The fleet has safely returned. Everyone, good work!

Starting A Sortie/Akizuki.Japanese: 第61駆逐隊、直ちに抜錨。出撃です！
Starting A Sortie/Akizuki.English: 61st DesDiv, setting sail immediately. Setting off!

Battle Start/Akizuki.Japanese: さあ、始めましょう。撃ち方、始め！
Battle Start/Akizuki.English: Now, shall we begin? Begin firing!

Attack/Akizuki.Japanese: この秋月が健在な限り、やらせはしません！
Attack/Akizuki.English: While this Akizuki still has strength, I won't let you!
Attack/Akizuki.Note: ⇧ shared with day/night special attacks, support expedition team arrival

Night Battle/Akizuki.Japanese: 秋月の夜戦、お見せしましょうか。
Night Battle/Akizuki.English: Akizuki's night battle, shall I show it to you?

Night Attack/Akizuki.Japanese: 弾幕が薄い…ような気がします。弾幕です！
Night Attack/Akizuki.English: I feel like... the barrage is light. Barrage!

MVP/Akizuki.Japanese: 秋月、艦隊をお守りしました。大丈夫、次もきっと、大丈夫です！
MVP/Akizuki.English: Akizuki protected the fleet. It's alright, next time, too, will be alright!

Minor Damage 1/Akizuki.English: Kugh! I can still go on!

Minor Damage 2/Akizuki.Japanese: 魚雷の誘爆を防いで！ 大丈夫！
Minor Damage 2/Akizuki.English: Don't let it detonate the torpedoes! It's alright !

Major Damage/Akizuki.Japanese: まだ…まだ、沈みません！艦隊の防空を…私はっ！
Major Damage/Akizuki.English: Not yet... I won't sink yet! The fleet's anti-air... I will-!

Major Damage/Akizuki Kai.Japanese: 被弾！？ 魚雷を全て放棄して、誘爆を防いで！ まだ……まだ大丈夫！
Major Damage/Akizuki Kai.English: Hit!? Abandon all torpedoes, prevent detonation!... not yet... I can keep going!

Sunk/Akizuki.Japanese: 翔鶴さんも…大鳳さんも…健在？　ふぅ…、大丈夫…艦隊は…だいじょう…ぶ…
Sunk/Akizuki.English: Shoukaku-san... Taihou-san... are you well? Ugh..., alright... the fleet is... alri... ght...

00:00/Akizuki.Japanese: 司令、この秋月が、時刻を報告します。現在時刻、マルマルマルマル、です！
00:00/Akizuki.English: Commander, Akizuki will report the time. The current time is 0000!

01:00/Akizuki.Japanese: マルヒトマルマルをご報告します。こんな形でよろしいでしょうか、司令？
01:00/Akizuki.English: The 0100 report. Is this the right way, Commander?

02:00/Akizuki.Japanese: マルフタマルマルです。今夜は月が…月が綺麗ですね、司令。ん、司令？
02:00/Akizuki.English: 0200. The moon tonight... the moon sure is beautiful, commander. Eh, commander?
02:00/Akizuki.Note: A reference to an anecdotal incident where Meiji era writer Natsume Sōseki, during his time as an English teacher, suggested to his students that the English phrase "I love you" be translated as "The moon is beautiful" (月が綺麗ですね).

03:00/Akizuki.Japanese: マルサンマルマルです、司令。この時間はとても静かですね。本当に静かです…
03:00/Akizuki.English: 0300, Commander. It's very quiet at this time. It's really quiet...

04:00/Akizuki.Japanese: マルヨンマルマルです。司令、眠くはありませんか？　濃い目のお茶、入れましょう。
04:00/Akizuki.English: 0400. Commander, are you not tired?　Let's have some strong tea.

05:00/Akizuki.Japanese: マルゴーマルマルとなりました、司令。はい。秋月、総員起こしの準備、了解です！
05:00/Akizuki.English: It is now 0500. Commander. Yes. Akizuki, prepared to wake everyone, roger!

06:00/Akizuki.Japanese: マルロクマルマルです。おはようございます、司令。はい、気持ちのよい朝ですね♪
06:00/Akizuki.English: 0600. Good morning, Commander. Yes, it is a nice morning♪

07:00/Akizuki.Japanese: マルナナマルマルです。司令、朝食の御用意、こちらです。簡単で…すみません
07:00/Akizuki.English: 0700. Commander, I'm preparing breakfast over here. I'm sorry that it's... simple.

08:00/Akizuki.Japanese: マルハチマルマル。第六一駆逐隊、出撃準備、完了です。いつでも抜錨、出来ます！
08:00/Akizuki.English: 0800. 61st DesDiv, sortie preparations complete. We can set sail at any time!

09:00/Akizuki.Japanese: マルキュウマルマルです。護衛する主力艦は戦艦？　空母ですか？　お任せください♪
09:00/Akizuki.English: 0900. The capital ship of the escort is a battleship? Carrier? Leave it to me!

10:00/Akizuki.Japanese: ヒトマルマルマルをご報告します。司令、演習もしっかりこなしていきたいですね
10:00/Akizuki.English: It's the 1000 report. Commander, I wish to properly complete the exercises as well.

11:00/Akizuki.Japanese: ヒトヒトマルマルです。司令、お昼はどうなさいますか？　秋月がご用意しましょうか？
11:00/Akizuki.English: 1100. Commander, what will you have for lunch? Shall I prepare it for you?

12:00/Akizuki.Japanese: ヒトフタマルマルです。司令、握り飯と沢庵のお昼です。あ…簡単で、すいません…
12:00/Akizuki.English: 1200. Commander, lunch is rice balls and pickled radish. Ah, sorry that it's simple...
12:00/Akizuki.Note: *Food was in short supply towards the end of the war and even the comparatively extravagant IJN had to cut down as much as they could afford on rations, hence the simple meal.

13:00/Akizuki.Japanese: ヒトサンマルマルとなりました。司令、すみません。夕食は豪華に頑張りますから！
13:00/Akizuki.English: It is now 1300. Commander, I apologize. I'll try my best to prepare a wonderful dinner!

14:00/Akizuki.Japanese: ヒトヨンマルマルです。初月、元気かなぁ…あ、司令。午後も頑張りましょう！
14:00/Akizuki.English: 1400. I wonder how Hatsuzuki is... Ah, Commander. Let's do our best in the afternoon too!

15:00/Akizuki.Japanese: ヒトゴーマルマルです。あ、はい。明石さんにもとってもお世話になりました。
15:00/Akizuki.English: 1500. Ah, yes. I've been in the care of Akashi-san.

16:00/Akizuki.Japanese: ヒトロクマルマルです。はい、後部にも高射装置を付けましたから、もう万全です！
16:00/Akizuki.English: 1600. Yes, I've attached an anti-air fire director on the stern as well. It's perfect!

17:00/Akizuki.Japanese: ヒトナナマルマルをご報告します。日が落ちますから、対空警戒もここまでですね。
17:00/Akizuki.English: It's the 1700 report. The sun is setting, so the anti-aircraft watch is ending.

18:00/Akizuki.Japanese: ヒトハチマルマルとなりました。はい、夕食の準備、秋月、豪華に頑張ります！
18:00/Akizuki.English: It is now 1800. Yes, Akizuki will do her best to prepare a wonderful dinner!

19:00/Akizuki.Japanese: ヒトキュウマルマルです！　熱々の麦飯、沢庵、そして牛缶に、お味噌汁も♪　どう？
19:00/Akizuki.English: 1900! Piping hot barley and rice, pickled radish, also canned beef, and miso soup♪ How is it?
19:00/Akizuki.Note: *Although more along the lines of an ordinary meal today, this would be considered extravagant due to low food supply. See 12:00 note

20:00/Akizuki.Japanese: フタマルマルマル。はい、秋月、今日はすこし奮発してしまいました。どうでした？
20:00/Akizuki.English: 2000. Yes, today, I pushed myself a bit extra. How was I?

21:00/Akizuki.Japanese: フタヒトマルマルです。え、涼月ですか？　はい、自慢の妹ですよ。ええ！
21:00/Akizuki.English: 2100. Eh, Suzutsuki? Yes, she's a little sister I'm proud of. Ei!

22:00/Akizuki.Japanese: フタフタマルマル。あ、翔鶴さん、瑞鶴さん。お疲れ様です。はい、大丈夫です！
22:00/Akizuki.English: 2200. Ah, Shoukaku-san, Zuikaku-san. Good work. Yes, I'm alright!

23:00/Akizuki.Japanese: フタサンマルマル。少し、緊張しました。はぁ…司令、本日も大変お疲れ様でした。
23:00/Akizuki.English: 2300. I was a bit nervous. Haa... Commander, very good work today.

Summer 2019 Event/Akizuki.Japanese: 秋月、推参。突入了解。やらせませ！
Summer 2019 Event/Akizuki.English: Akizuki has arrived. Understood, charging in. I won't let them beat me!

Christmas 2014/Akizuki.Japanese: メリー・クリスマスです、司令！秋月、七面鳥を焼いたんですよ。あっ、だめっ！？何で！？
Christmas 2014/Akizuki.English: Merry Christmas, Commander! I roasted a turkey! Ah, I shouldn’t have!? Why!?

New Year 2015/Akizuki.Japanese: あけましておめでとうございます、司令！本年も、どうぞよろしくお願い致します！
New Year 2015/Akizuki.English: Happy New Year, Commander! Please treat me well this year too!

2nd Anniversary/Akizuki.Japanese: 二周年おめでとうございます司令！これからも秋月、艦隊防空がんばります！
2nd Anniversary/Akizuki.English: Congratulations on the 2nd anniversary, Commander! I’ll continue to work hard doing fleet air defense!

3rd Anniversary/Akizuki.Japanese: アーケード？司令、アーケードって何ですか？…ふむふむ。秋月、勉強になります！
3rd Anniversary/Akizuki.English: Arcade? What’s an “arcade”, Commander? …I see, I see. I learned something!

Autumn 2019/Akizuki.Japanese: 秋月、鎮守府秋祭り、全力で参加します。テルちゃん、ハツちゃん、司令、一緒に行きましょう！
Autumn 2019/Akizuki.English: I, Akizuki, will be giving my all for the Naval District Autumn Festival. Teru, Hatsu, Commander, let's go together!

Saury 2019/Akizuki.Japanese: 秋月、秋刀魚漁場の保護と秋刀魚漁支援、全力で事を当たります。そうです、やらせませ！
Saury 2019/Akizuki.English: I'll do my best to protect the saury fisheries and support the saury fishing. That's right, leave it to me!

7th Anniversary/Akizuki.Japanese: 今日は大切な日ですね。大丈夫、秋月もご一緒します、司令。秋月も嬉しいです。
7th Anniversary/Akizuki.English: Today is an important day. Don't worry, I'll be by your side, Commander. I'm happy too.
